    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" xml:id="p.1"/>
                <opener>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine rendition="#c">
                            <persName key="pers.3263">Arnold
                            Schoenberg</persName>
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine rendition="#c">
                            <placeName key="place.15.7.3.1">116 N. Rockingham
                                Ave.</placeName>
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine rendition="#c">Los Angeles 24, California.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1949-04-09">April 9, 1949</date>.</dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr <persName key="pers.3204">Alfred Schlee</persName>
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            <orgName key="org.1">Universal Edition</orgName>
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Wien I</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            <placeName key="place.9.11.6.12">Karlsplatz
                            6</placeName>
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Musikvereinsgebäude</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </opener>
                <salute>Dear Mr <persName key="pers.3204">Schlee</persName>:</salute>
                <p>I need urgently two sets of the <bibl sameAs="werke.54">Pierrot
                        <lb/>lunaire</bibl>, parts and score. One for Mr <seg type="comment"
                                ><orig><persName key="pers.1102">Kurt
                            Frederick</persName></orig><note xml:id="nx4b_nvd_gfc" resp="#KBleier"
                                ><persName key="pers.1102">Kurt Frederick</persName>, der <bibl
                                sameAs="werke.54">Pierrot lunaire op. 21</bibl> vor seiner
                            Emigration (unter seinem ursprünglichen Namen Fuchsgelb) mehrfach
                            aufgeführt hatte, bekundete sein Interesse an einer Aufführung bereits
                                <date when="1947">1947</date> (Kurt Frederick an Arnold Schönberg,
                            30. Mai 1947; <ref
                                target="https://repo.schoenberg.at/urn:nbn:at:at-asc-B106861">ASCC
                                10686</ref>). Infolge der Kriegsumstände und missverständlicher
                            Kommunikation gestaltete sich die Materialbeschaffung kompliziert. <date
                                when="1950">1950</date> wurde der Plan einer Aufführung wegen
                            Fehlens eines geeigneten Cellisten verworfen (Kurt Frederick an Arnold
                            Schönberg, 2. März 1950; <ref
                                target="https://repo.schoenberg.at/urn:nbn:at:at-asc-B107008">ASCC
                                10700</ref>)</note>
                    </seg>
                    <lb/>who <seg type="comment">
                        <orig>performed</orig>
                        <note xml:id="nxrs_453_vfc" resp="#KBleier">
                            <ref target="event.180"/>
                        </note>
                    </seg> my <bibl sameAs="werke.77">Survivor from Warsaw</bibl>, in <placeName
                        key="place.15.18">Albuquerque</placeName>
                    <lb/>and wants to perform now <bibl sameAs="werke.54">Pierrot Lunaire</bibl> and
                    the other <lb/>for a performance in <placeName
                        key="place.15.5">Chicago</placeName>.</p>
                <p>The <orgName key="org.23">Associated Music Publishers</orgName> have not one copy
                    <lb/>of this piece which they can loan for more than a <lb/>few days. Besides,
                    my own set is incomplete as some<g ref="#typoHyphen"/>
                    <lb break="no"/>one has failed to return the clarinet part. I don’t know
                    <lb/>who. And I would like to have this set completed, will <lb/>you send me
                    also, besides these two copies, one clarinet <lb/>part. I hope you can fulfill
                    this at once and I want <lb/>you to see to it that Mr <persName key="pers.2106">Leibowitz</persName> receives the parts <lb/>as fast as possible, because
                        <seg type="comment">
                        <orig>he writes me</orig>
                        <note xml:id="ngdj_k4n_zfc" resp="#KBleier">Neben Informationen über das geplante Konzert am <ref target="event.191"/> äußerte <persName key="pers.2106">René
                                Leibowitz </persName>den Eindruck, dass ihm die <orgName key="org.1">UE</orgName> nur widerwillig das Aufführungsmaterial zur Verfügung
                            stellen wolle. Er vermutete den Grund darin, dass <persName key="pers.3204">Schlee</persName>
                            <persName key="pers.2106">Leibowitz'</persName> Aufführung in Konkurrenz
                            zum Pierrot lunaire Ensemble mit seiner Ehefrau <persName key="pers.1518">Annemarie Hegner</persName> betrachte und bat
                                <persName key="pers.3263">Schönberg</persName>, selbst an die
                                <orgName key="org.1">UE</orgName> zu schreiben (René Leibowitz
                            an Arnold Schönberg, 5. April 1949; <ref target="https://repo.schoenberg.at/urn:nbn:at:at-asc-B137424">ASCC
                                13742</ref>)</note>
                    </seg> he wants already <lb/>to start slowly to
                    study with his performers the piece <lb/>for his performance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute rendition="#r">I am most sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <lb/>
                    <persName key="pers.1608">R. H.</persName>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
